<p>An alternative method for clustering Mahalanobis distances to the center of mass can be calculated. The Mahalanobis distance 
 <italic>d</italic> of an object 
 <italic>a</italic> to the center 
 <italic>b</italic> is defined as [
 <xref rid="B83-pharmaceuticals-12-00157" ref-type="bibr">83</xref>]:
 <disp-formula id="FD8-pharmaceuticals-12-00157">
  <label>(8)</label>
  <math id="mm11">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>d</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <mrow>
       <mi>a</mi>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>b</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msqrt>
      <mrow>
       <msup>
        <mrow>
         <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
           <mi>a</mi>
           <mo>−</mo>
           <mi>b</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mi>T</mi>
       </msup>
       <msup>
        <mi>V</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mo>−</mo>
         <mn>1</mn>
        </mrow>
       </msup>
       <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
       <mi>a</mi>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mi>b</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msqrt>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
     <mo>,</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
